        "import os\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "import subprocess\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 1. Environment & Dependency Setup ---\n",
        "def install_dependencies():\n",
        "    packages = [\"pvlib\", \"optuna\", \"xgboost\", \"torch\", \"scikit-learn\", \"pandas\", \"numpy\"]\n",
        "    print(f\"Installing dependencies: {', '.join(packages)}...\")\n",
        "    subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \"-m\", \"pip\", \"install\"] + packages)\n",
        "    print(\"Dependencies installed.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "install_dependencies()\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 2. Project Structure Definition ---\n",
        "PROJECT_ROOT = \"/content/solar_forecast_project\"\n",
        "DIRS = [\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/raw\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/data/processed\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/models/checkpoints\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/src/config\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/src/data\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/src/features\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/src/models\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/src/training\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/src/evaluation\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/src/utils\",\n",
        "    f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/tests\",\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "for d in DIRS:\n",
        "    os.makedirs(d, exist_ok=True)\n",
        "    with open(f\"{d}/__init__.py\", 'w') as f: pass # Make directories importable\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Project structure created at {PROJECT_ROOT}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 3. Writing Source Code Modules ---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Helper to write files\n",
        "def write_module(path, content):\n",
        "    full_path = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/{path}\"\n",
        "    with open(full_path, \"w\") as f:\n",
        "        f.write(content)\n",
        "    print(f\"Created: {path}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# A. CONFIGURATION (Based on Paper Table VI and Section 3)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/config/settings.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "\n",
        "class Config:\n",
        "    # Paths\n",
        "    ROOT_DIR = Path(\"/content/solar_forecast_project\")\n",
        "    DATA_RAW = ROOT_DIR / \"data/raw\"\n",
        "    DATA_PROCESSED = ROOT_DIR / \"data/processed\"\n",
        "    MODEL_DIR = ROOT_DIR / \"models/checkpoints\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Global\n",
        "    SEED = 42\n",
        "    TIME_COL = \"timestamp\"\n",
        "    TARGET_COL = \"power_generation\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Physics Constants (Paper Eq 1)\n",
        "    IRRADIANCE_THRESHOLD = 10  # Watts/m^2 (Guard for night detection)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Feature Engineering (Paper Section 3.D)\n",
        "    LAGS = [1, 4, 96, 192, 672]  # 15-min intervals: 1h, 4h, 1d, 2d, 1w\n",
        "    ROLLING_WINDOWS = [4, 16, 96] # 1h, 4h, 24h\n",
        "\n",
        "    # XGBoost Hyperparameters (Paper Table VI)\n",
        "    XGB_PARAMS = {\n",
        "        'n_estimators': 92,\n",
        "        'max_depth': 8,\n",
        "        'learning_rate': 0.1236,\n",
        "        'subsample': 0.8737,\n",
        "        'colsample_bytree': 0.7607,\n",
        "        'reg_alpha': 0.0749, # L1\n",
        "        'reg_lambda': 3.3773, # L2\n",
        "        'objective': 'reg:squarederror',\n",
        "        'tree_method': 'hist',\n",
        "        'n_jobs': -1,\n",
        "        'random_state': SEED\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    # LSTM Hyperparameters (Paper Table VI)\n",
        "    LSTM_PARAMS = {\n",
        "        'hidden_dim': 64,\n",
        "        'num_layers': 2,\n",
        "        'lookback_window': 24, # 6 hours (24 * 15mins)\n",
        "        'learning_rate': 0.001,\n",
        "        'epochs': 25,\n",
        "        'batch_size': 128\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# B. UTILITIES (Logging & Seeding)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/utils/logger.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import logging\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "import random\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "def setup_logger(name=\"SolarForecast\"):\n",
        "    logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n",
        "    logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)\n",
        "    if not logger.handlers:\n",
        "        handler = logging.StreamHandler(sys.stdout)\n",
        "        formatter = logging.Formatter('%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s')\n",
        "        handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n",
        "        logger.addHandler(handler)\n",
        "    return logger\n",
        "\n",
        "def seed_everything(seed=42):\n",
        "    random.seed(seed)\n",
        "    os.environ['PYTHONHASHSEED'] = str(seed)\n",
        "    np.random.seed(seed)\n",
        "    torch.manual_seed(seed)\n",
        "    torch.cuda.manual_seed(seed)\n",
        "    torch.backends.cudnn.deterministic = True\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# C. PHYSICS & PREPROCESSING (Paper Section 3.A: Ineichen Model & Imputation)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/data/physics.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pvlib\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "\n",
        "class PhysicsEngine:\n",
        "    @staticmethod\n",
        "    def calculate_clear_sky(lat, lon, times, elevation=0):\n",
        "        # Using Ineichen model as per Paper Eq (3)\n",
        "        site = pvlib.location.Location(lat, lon, altitude=elevation)\n",
        "        cs = site.get_clearsky(times, model='ineichen')\n",
        "        return cs # Returns GHI, DNI, DHI\n",
        "\n",
        "    @staticmethod\n",
        "    def detect_nighttime(ghi_series, elevation_series, threshold=Config.IRRADIANCE_THRESHOLD):\n",
        "        # Paper Eq (1): Night if Elevation <= 0 or GHI < threshold\n",
        "        is_night = (elevation_series <= 0) | (ghi_series < threshold)\n",
        "        return is_night\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "write_module(\"src/data/preprocessor.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.experimental import enable_iterative_imputer\n",
        "from sklearn.impute import IterativeImputer\n",
        "from .physics import PhysicsEngine\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"Preprocessor\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class DataPipeline:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, lat, lon, elevation):\n",
        "        self.lat = lat\n",
        "        self.lon = lon\n",
        "        self.elevation = elevation\n",
        "\n",
        "    def memory_optimize(self, df):\n",
        "        # Paper Section 3.A.5: Dtype downcasting\n",
        "        fcols = df.select_dtypes('float').columns\n",
        "        icols = df.select_dtypes('integer').columns\n",
        "        df[fcols] = df[fcols].apply(pd.to_numeric, downcast='float')\n",
        "        df[icols] = df[icols].apply(pd.to_numeric, downcast='integer')\n",
        "        return df\n",
        "\n",
        "    def impute_physics_guided(self, df):\n",
        "        # Paper Eq (2): Domain-guided imputation\n",
        "        logger.info(\"Applying physics-guided imputation...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 1. Calculate Solar Position & Clear Sky\n",
        "        times = pd.DatetimeIndex(df[Config.TIME_COL])\n",
        "        solpos = pvlib.solarposition.get_solarposition(times, self.lat, self.lon)\n",
        "        df['elevation'] = solpos['elevation'].values\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Nighttime Imputation (Set to 0)\n",
        "        is_night = PhysicsEngine.detect_nighttime(df['ghi'], df['elevation'])\n",
        "        # If PV is NaN and it's night, fill 0\n",
        "        mask_night_nan = df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna() & is_night\n",
        "        df.loc[mask_night_nan, Config.TARGET_COL] = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Daytime Imputation (Iterative)\n",
        "        # Only fit imputer on daytime data to avoid bias\n",
        "        day_mask = ~is_night\n",
        "        if df.loc[day_mask, Config.TARGET_COL].isna().sum() > 0:\n",
        "            logger.info(\"Imputing daytime gaps with MICE...\")\n",
        "            imputer = IterativeImputer(max_iter=10, random_state=Config.SEED)\n",
        "            cols_to_use = ['ghi', 'dni', 'dhi', 'temp', 'humidity', Config.TARGET_COL]\n",
        "            # Filter available columns\n",
        "            cols = [c for c in cols_to_use if c in df.columns]\n",
        "\n",
        "            imputed_data = imputer.fit_transform(df.loc[day_mask, cols])\n",
        "            df.loc[day_mask, cols] = imputed_data\n",
        "\n",
        "        return df\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# D. FEATURE ENGINEERING (Paper Section 3.D)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/features/engineer.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "\n",
        "class FeatureEngineer:\n",
        "    def process(self, df):\n",
        "        df = df.sort_values(Config.TIME_COL).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 1. Time Features (Cyclical encoding Eq 24, 25)\n",
        "        dt = pd.to_datetime(df[Config.TIME_COL])\n",
        "        df['hour_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.hour / 24)\n",
        "        df['hour_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.hour / 24)\n",
        "        df['doy_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.dayofyear / 365)\n",
        "        df['doy_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.dayofyear / 365)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Lag Features (Eq 26)\n",
        "        # Note: We must be careful not to leak future info.\n",
        "        # Standard approach: Shift target variable.\n",
        "        for lag in Config.LAGS:\n",
        "            df[f'lag_{lag}'] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].shift(lag)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Rolling Statistics (Eq 27)\n",
        "        for w in Config.ROLLING_WINDOWS:\n",
        "            df[f'roll_mean_{w}'] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].shift(1).rolling(window=w).mean()\n",
        "            df[f'roll_std_{w}'] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].shift(1).rolling(window=w).std()\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 4. Irradiance Normalization (Eq 4) - Clear Sky Index\n",
        "        # Assuming 'ghi' (measured) and 'ghi_cs' (clear sky) exist\n",
        "        if 'ghi' in df.columns and 'ghi_cs' in df.columns:\n",
        "            # Avoid division by zero\n",
        "            df['k_t'] = df['ghi'] / (df['ghi_cs'] + 1e-5)\n",
        "\n",
        "        return df.dropna().reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# E. MODELS: XGBoost (Stage 1)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/xgb_component.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import xgboost as xgb\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"XGBoost\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class XGBModel:\n",
        "    def __init__(self):\n",
        "        self.model = xgb.XGBRegressor(**Config.XGB_PARAMS)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, X, y, X_val=None, y_val=None):\n",
        "        eval_set = [(X_val, y_val)] if X_val is not None else None\n",
        "        self.model.fit(X, y, eval_set=eval_set, verbose=False)\n",
        "        logger.info(\"XGBoost training complete.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    def predict(self, X):\n",
        "        return self.model.predict(X)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def get_residuals(self, X, y_true):\n",
        "        y_pred = self.predict(X)\n",
        "        return y_true - y_pred\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# F. MODELS: LSTM + Heteroscedastic Loss (Stage 2)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/lstm_component.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "\n",
        "# Paper Eq (7): LSTM Architecture\n",
        "class ResidualLSTM(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers):\n",
        "        super(ResidualLSTM, self).__init__()\n",
        "        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, batch_first=True)\n",
        "        # Output: Correction (Delta) and Log Variance (log sigma^2)\n",
        "        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_dim, 2)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        # x shape: (batch, seq_len, features)\n",
        "        out, _ = self.lstm(x)\n",
        "        out = out[:, -1, :] # Take last time step\n",
        "        return self.fc(out) # returns [delta, log_var]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Paper Eq (9): Heteroscedastic Loss\n",
        "class HeteroscedasticLoss(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self):\n",
        "        super(HeteroscedasticLoss, self).__init__()\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, pred, target):\n",
        "        # pred: [delta, log_var]\n",
        "        # target: residual (r_t)\n",
        "        delta = pred[:, 0]\n",
        "        log_var = pred[:, 1]\n",
        "        residual = target.squeeze()\n",
        "\n",
        "        precision = torch.exp(-log_var)\n",
        "        loss = 0.5 * precision * (residual - delta)**2 + 0.5 * log_var\n",
        "        return loss.mean()\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# G. HYBRID ORCHESTRATOR\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/hybrid_system.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, TensorDataset\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from .xgb_component import XGBModel\n",
        "from .lstm_component import ResidualLSTM, HeteroscedasticLoss\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"HybridSystem\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class HybridForecaster:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim_lstm):\n",
        "        self.xgb_model = XGBModel()\n",
        "        self.lstm_model = ResidualLSTM(\n",
        "            input_dim=input_dim_lstm,\n",
        "            hidden_dim=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['hidden_dim'],\n",
        "            num_layers=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['num_layers']\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm = StandardScaler()\n",
        "        self.device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, X_train_df, y_train, X_val_df=None, y_val=None):\n",
        "        # 1. Train XGBoost\n",
        "        logger.info(\"Phase 1: Training XGBoost...\")\n",
        "        self.xgb_model.fit(X_train_df, y_train, X_val_df, y_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Calculate Residuals\n",
        "        r_train = self.xgb_model.get_residuals(X_train_df, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Prepare LSTM Data (Create sequences of residuals)\n",
        "        # We model temporal dependency of residuals\n",
        "        logger.info(\"Phase 2: Preparing LSTM sequences...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Reshape residuals for LSTM: (Samples, Lookback, 1)\n",
        "        # Note: In a real scenario, we might add other exogenous vars to LSTM input\n",
        "        r_train = r_train.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm.fit(r_train)\n",
        "        r_train_scaled = self.scaler_lstm.transform(r_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        X_lstm, y_lstm = self._create_sequences(r_train_scaled, Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'])\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 4. Train LSTM\n",
        "        logger.info(\"Phase 3: Training LSTM on residuals...\")\n",
        "        self._train_lstm(X_lstm, y_lstm)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def predict(self, X_df, return_uncertainty=False):\n",
        "        # 1. XGBoost Base Prediction\n",
        "        y_xgb = self.xgb_model.predict(X_df)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. LSTM Residual Correction\n",
        "        # Note: In inference, we need the PAST residuals.\n",
        "        # For this simplified architecture, we assume we have a stream of past residuals.\n",
        "        # This part requires careful handling in production (streaming state).\n",
        "        # Here we mock the residual sequence generation for the demo.\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Placeholder: In strict testing, we'd generate residuals sequentially.\n",
        "        # For batch processing demo:\n",
        "        dummy_resid = np.zeros((len(X_df), Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'], 1))\n",
        "        dummy_tensor = torch.FloatTensor(dummy_resid).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.eval()\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            preds = self.lstm_model(dummy_tensor).cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        delta = preds[:, 0]\n",
        "        log_var = preds[:, 1]\n",
        "        sigma = np.sqrt(np.exp(log_var))\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Inverse transform delta (simplified)\n",
        "        delta_real = delta * self.scaler_lstm.scale_[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Combine (Eq 8)\n",
        "        y_hybrid = y_xgb + delta_real\n",
        "\n",
        "        if return_uncertainty:\n",
        "            return y_hybrid, sigma\n",
        "        return y_hybrid\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _create_sequences(self, data, seq_len):\n",
        "        xs, ys = [], []\n",
        "        for i in range(len(data) - seq_len):\n",
        "            x = data[i:(i + seq_len)]\n",
        "            y = data[i + seq_len]\n",
        "            xs.append(x)\n",
        "            ys.append(y)\n",
        "        return torch.FloatTensor(np.array(xs)).to(self.device), torch.FloatTensor(np.array(ys)).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _train_lstm(self, X, y):\n",
        "        optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(self.lstm_model.parameters(), lr=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['learning_rate'])\n",
        "        criterion = HeteroscedasticLoss()\n",
        "\n",
        "        dataset = TensorDataset(X, y)\n",
        "        loader = DataLoader(dataset, batch_size=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['batch_size'], shuffle=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "        for epoch in range(Config.LSTM_PARAMS['epochs']):\n",
        "            self.lstm_model.train()\n",
        "            total_loss = 0\n",
        "            for batch_X, batch_y in loader:\n",
        "                optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
        "                preds = self.lstm_model(batch_X)\n",
        "                loss = criterion(preds, batch_y)\n",
        "                loss.backward()\n",
        "                optimizer.step()\n",
        "                total_loss += loss.item()\n",
        "            if (epoch+1) % 5 == 0:\n",
        "                logger.info(f\"LSTM Epoch {epoch+1}: Loss {total_loss/len(loader):.4f}\")\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# H. EVALUATION METRICS (Paper Table V)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/evaluation/metrics.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error\n",
        "\n",
        "def calculate_metrics(y_true, y_pred, y_std=None):\n",
        "    rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))\n",
        "    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "    metrics = {\"RMSE\": rmse, \"MAE\": mae}\n",
        "\n",
        "    if y_std is not None:\n",
        "        # Eq 32: PICP (Prediction Interval Coverage Probability)\n",
        "        lower = y_pred - 1.96 * y_std\n",
        "        upper = y_pred + 1.96 * y_std\n",
        "        within_bounds = ((y_true >= lower) & (y_true <= upper))\n",
        "        picp = np.mean(within_bounds)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Eq 33: MPIW (Mean Prediction Interval Width)\n",
        "        mpiw = np.mean(upper - lower)\n",
        "\n",
        "        metrics[\"PICP\"] = picp\n",
        "        metrics[\"MPIW\"] = mpiw\n",
        "\n",
        "    return metrics\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# I. MAIN EXECUTION SCRIPT\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"main.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "from src.config.settings import Config\n",
        "from src.utils.logger import setup_logger, seed_everything\n",
        "from src.data.preprocessor import DataPipeline\n",
        "from src.features.engineer import FeatureEngineer\n",
        "from src.models.hybrid_system import HybridForecaster\n",
        "from src.evaluation.metrics import calculate_metrics\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    logger = setup_logger(\"Main\")\n",
        "    seed_everything(Config.SEED)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 1. Dummy Data Generation (Replace with pd.read_csv(Config.DATA_RAW / 'unisolar.csv'))\n",
        "    logger.info(\"Generating dummy data for structure validation...\")\n",

        "write_module(\"src/utils/logger.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import logging\n",

        "\n",
        "def setup_logger(name=\"SolarForecast\"):\n",

        "    return logger\n",
        "\n",
        "def seed_everything(seed=42):\n",

        "    os.environ['PYTHONHASHSEED'] = str(seed)\n",
        "    np.random.seed(seed)\n",
        "    torch.manual_seed(seed)\n",
        "    torch.cuda.manual_seed(seed)\n",

        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# C. PHYSICS & PREPROCESSING (Crucial for your 53% missing data)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/data/physics.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pvlib\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "\n",
        "class PhysicsEngine:\n",
        "    @staticmethod\n",
        "    def detect_nighttime(ghi_series, threshold=Config.IRRADIANCE_THRESHOLD):\n",
        "        # If Irradiance is near 0, it is Night.\n",
        "        return ghi_series < threshold\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "write_module(\"src/data/preprocessor.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\n",
        "from .physics import PhysicsEngine\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"Preprocessor\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class DataPipeline:\n",
        "    def __init__(self):\n",
        "        pass\n",
        "\n",
        "    def process_and_impute(self, df):\n",
        "        # 1. Sort by time\n",
        "        df = df.sort_values(Config.TIME_COL).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Physics-Based Night Filling (The most important step)\n",
        "        # If GHI (Sun) is 0, Power MUST be 0.\n",
        "        # This fixes the 18,000 missing rows at night.\n",
        "        if 'ghi' in df.columns:\n",
        "            is_night = PhysicsEngine.detect_nighttime(df['ghi'])\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Count missing before fix\n",
        "            missing_before = df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna().sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Fill 0s where it's night and power is missing\n",
        "            mask = (df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna()) & (is_night)\n",
        "            df.loc[mask, Config.TARGET_COL] = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "            missing_after = df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna().sum()\n",
        "            logger.info(f\"Physics Imputation recovered {missing_before - missing_after} night-time rows.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Interpolate small daytime gaps (Linear)\n",
        "        # For remaining missing values (clouds/sensor glitches during day)\n",
        "        df[Config.TARGET_COL] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].interpolate(method='linear', limit=4)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 4. Drop any remaining huge gaps we can't fix\n",
        "        df = df.dropna(subset=[Config.TARGET_COL, 'ghi', 'temp'])\n",
        "\n",
        "        return df\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# D. FEATURE ENGINEERING\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/features/engineer.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "\n",
        "class FeatureEngineer:\n",
        "    def process(self, df):\n",
        "        df = df.copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 1. Time Features (Cyclical)\n",
        "        dt = pd.to_datetime(df[Config.TIME_COL])\n",
        "        df['hour_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.hour / 24)\n",
        "        df['hour_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.hour / 24)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Lag Features (What happened 15 mins ago? 1 hour ago?)\n",
        "        # IMPORTANT: Shift target to avoid data leakage\n",
        "        for lag in Config.LAGS:\n",
        "            df[f'lag_{lag}'] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].shift(lag)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Rolling Means (Trend)\n",
        "        for w in Config.ROLLING_WINDOWS:\n",
        "            df[f'roll_mean_{w}'] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].shift(1).rolling(window=w).mean()\n",
        "\n",
        "        return df.dropna().reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# E. MODELS (XGBoost + LSTM Hybrid)\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/xgb_component.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import xgboost as xgb\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"XGBoost\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class XGBModel:\n",
        "    def __init__(self):\n",
        "        self.model = xgb.XGBRegressor(**Config.XGB_PARAMS)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, X, y, X_val=None, y_val=None):\n",
        "        eval_set = [(X_val, y_val)] if X_val is not None else None\n",
        "        self.model.fit(X, y, eval_set=eval_set, verbose=False)\n",
        "        logger.info(\"XGBoost training complete.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    def predict(self, X):\n",
        "        return self.model.predict(X)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def get_residuals(self, X, y_true):\n",
        "        y_pred = self.predict(X)\n",
        "        return y_true - y_pred\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/lstm_component.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Residual Correction LSTM\n",
        "class ResidualLSTM(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers):\n",
        "        super(ResidualLSTM, self).__init__()\n",
        "        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, batch_first=True)\n",
        "        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_dim, 2) # Outputs: [Correction, Uncertainty]\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        out, _ = self.lstm(x)\n",
        "        out = out[:, -1, :]\n",
        "        return self.fc(out)\n",
        "\n",
        "class HeteroscedasticLoss(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def forward(self, pred, target):\n",
        "        delta = pred[:, 0]\n",
        "        log_var = pred[:, 1]\n",
        "        residual = target.squeeze()\n",
        "        precision = torch.exp(-log_var)\n",
        "        loss = 0.5 * precision * (residual - delta)**2 + 0.5 * log_var\n",
        "        return loss.mean()\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/hybrid_system.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, TensorDataset\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from .xgb_component import XGBModel\n",
        "from .lstm_component import ResidualLSTM, HeteroscedasticLoss\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"HybridSystem\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class HybridForecaster:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim_lstm):\n",
        "        self.xgb_model = XGBModel()\n",
        "        self.lstm_model = ResidualLSTM(\n",
        "            input_dim=input_dim_lstm,\n",
        "            hidden_dim=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['hidden_dim'],\n",
        "            num_layers=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['num_layers']\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm = StandardScaler()\n",
        "        self.device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val):\n",
        "        # Phase 1: XGBoost\n",
        "        logger.info(\"Training XGBoost Base Model...\")\n",
        "        self.xgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Phase 2: Residuals\n",
        "        r_train = self.xgb_model.get_residuals(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Prepare LSTM Data\n",
        "        r_train = r_train.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm.fit(r_train)\n",
        "        r_train_scaled = self.scaler_lstm.transform(r_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        X_lstm, y_lstm = self._create_sequences(r_train_scaled, Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'])\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Phase 3: Train LSTM\n",
        "        logger.info(f\"Training LSTM Residual Corrector on {self.device}...\")\n",
        "        self._train_lstm(X_lstm, y_lstm)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def predict(self, X_df):\n",
        "        # 1. Base Prediction\n",
        "        y_xgb = self.xgb_model.predict(X_df)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Residual Correction (Simplified for demo)\n",
        "        # Creating a dummy tensor for batch prediction speed\n",
        "        dummy_resid = np.zeros((len(X_df), Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'], 1))\n",
        "        dummy_tensor = torch.FloatTensor(dummy_resid).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.eval()\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            preds = self.lstm_model(dummy_tensor).cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        delta = preds[:, 0] * self.scaler_lstm.scale_[0] # Scale back\n",
        "        sigma = np.sqrt(np.exp(preds[:, 1]))\n",
        "\n",
        "        return y_xgb + delta, sigma\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _create_sequences(self, data, seq_len):\n",
        "        xs, ys = [], []\n",
        "        for i in range(len(data) - seq_len):\n",
        "            x = data[i:(i + seq_len)]\n",
        "            y = data[i + seq_len]\n",
        "            xs.append(x)\n",
        "            ys.append(y)\n",
        "        return torch.FloatTensor(np.array(xs)).to(self.device), torch.FloatTensor(np.array(ys)).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _train_lstm(self, X, y):\n",
        "        optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(self.lstm_model.parameters(), lr=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['learning_rate'])\n",
        "        criterion = HeteroscedasticLoss()\n",
        "        dataset = TensorDataset(X, y)\n",
        "        loader = DataLoader(dataset, batch_size=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['batch_size'], shuffle=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "        for epoch in range(Config.LSTM_PARAMS['epochs']):\n",
        "            self.lstm_model.train()\n",
        "            total_loss = 0\n",
        "            for batch_X, batch_y in loader:\n",
        "                optimizer.zero_grad()\n",

        "write_module(\"src/data/preprocessor.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",

        "\n",
        "class DataPipeline:\n",
        "    def __init__(self):\n",
        "        pass\n",
        "\n",
        "    def process_and_impute(self, df):\n",
        "        # 1. Sort by time\n",
        "        df = df.sort_values(Config.TIME_COL).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Physics-Based Night Filling (The most important step)\n",
        "        # If GHI (Sun) is 0, Power MUST be 0.\n",
        "        # This fixes the 18,000 missing rows at night.\n",

        "            is_night = PhysicsEngine.detect_nighttime(df['ghi'])\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Count missing before fix\n",
        "            missing_before = df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna().sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Fill 0s where it's night and power is missing\n",
        "            mask = (df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna()) & (is_night)\n",
        "            df.loc[mask, Config.TARGET_COL] = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "            missing_after = df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna().sum()\n",
        "            logger.info(f\"Physics Imputation recovered {missing_before - missing_after} night-time rows.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Interpolate small daytime gaps (Linear)\n",
        "        # For remaining missing values (clouds/sensor glitches during day)\n",
        "        df[Config.TARGET_COL] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].interpolate(method='linear', limit=4)\n",

        "class FeatureEngineer:\n",

        "        dt = pd.to_datetime(df[Config.TIME_COL])\n",
        "        df['hour_sin'] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.hour / 24)\n",
        "        df['hour_cos'] = np.cos(2 * np.pi * dt.dt.hour / 24)\n",

        "        # 2. Lag Features (What happened 15 mins ago? 1 hour ago?)\n",
        "        # IMPORTANT: Shift target to avoid data leakage\n",
        "        for lag in Config.LAGS:\n",
        "            df[f'lag_{lag}'] = df[Config.TARGET_COL].shift(lag)\n",

        "write_module(\"src/models/lstm_component.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Residual Correction LSTM\n",
        "class ResidualLSTM(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers):\n",
        "        super(ResidualLSTM, self).__init__()\n",
        "        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, batch_first=True)\n",
        "        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_dim, 2) # Outputs: [Correction, Uncertainty]\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        out, _ = self.lstm(x)\n",
        "        out = out[:, -1, :]\n",
        "        return self.fc(out)\n",
        "\n",
        "class HeteroscedasticLoss(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def forward(self, pred, target):\n",
        "        delta = pred[:, 0]\n",
        "        log_var = pred[:, 1]\n",
        "        residual = target.squeeze()\n",
        "        precision = torch.exp(-log_var)\n",
        "        loss = 0.5 * precision * (residual - delta)**2 + 0.5 * log_var\n",
        "        return loss.mean()\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",
        "\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/hybrid_system.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, TensorDataset\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from .xgb_component import XGBModel\n",
        "from .lstm_component import ResidualLSTM, HeteroscedasticLoss\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"HybridSystem\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class HybridForecaster:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim_lstm):\n",
        "        self.xgb_model = XGBModel()\n",
        "        self.lstm_model = ResidualLSTM(\n",
        "            input_dim=input_dim_lstm,\n",
        "            hidden_dim=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['hidden_dim'],\n",
        "            num_layers=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['num_layers']\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm = StandardScaler()\n",
        "        self.device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val):\n",
        "        # Phase 1: XGBoost\n",
        "        logger.info(\"Training XGBoost Base Model...\")\n",
        "        self.xgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Phase 2: Residuals\n",
        "        r_train = self.xgb_model.get_residuals(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Prepare LSTM Data\n",
        "        r_train = r_train.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm.fit(r_train)\n",
        "        r_train_scaled = self.scaler_lstm.transform(r_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        X_lstm, y_lstm = self._create_sequences(r_train_scaled, Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'])\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Phase 3: Train LSTM\n",
        "        logger.info(f\"Training LSTM Residual Corrector on {self.device}...\")\n",
        "        self._train_lstm(X_lstm, y_lstm)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def predict(self, X_df):\n",
        "        # 1. Base Prediction\n",
        "        y_xgb = self.xgb_model.predict(X_df)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Residual Correction (Simplified for demo)\n",
        "        # Creating a dummy tensor for batch prediction speed\n",
        "        dummy_resid = np.zeros((len(X_df), Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'], 1))\n",
        "        dummy_tensor = torch.FloatTensor(dummy_resid).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.eval()\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            preds = self.lstm_model(dummy_tensor).cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        delta = preds[:, 0] * self.scaler_lstm.scale_[0] # Scale back\n",
        "        sigma = np.sqrt(np.exp(preds[:, 1]))\n",
        "\n",
        "        return y_xgb + delta, sigma\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _create_sequences(self, data, seq_len):\n",
        "        xs, ys = [], []\n",
        "        for i in range(len(data) - seq_len):\n",
        "            x = data[i:(i + seq_len)]\n",
        "            y = data[i + seq_len]\n",
        "            xs.append(x)\n",
        "            ys.append(y)\n",
        "        return torch.FloatTensor(np.array(xs)).to(self.device), torch.FloatTensor(np.array(ys)).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _train_lstm(self, X, y):\n",
        "        optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(self.lstm_model.parameters(), lr=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['learning_rate'])\n",

        "write_module(\"src/data/preprocessor.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",

        "class DataPipeline:\n",

        "    def process_and_impute(self, df):\n",
        "        # 1. Sort by time\n",

        "            # Count missing before fix\n",

        "\n",
        "            # Fill 0s where it's night and power is missing\n",
        "            mask = (df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna()) & (is_night)\n",
        "            df.loc[mask, Config.TARGET_COL] = 0.0\n",
        "\n",
        "            missing_after = df[Config.TARGET_COL].isna().sum()\n",
        "            logger.info(f\"Physics Imputation recovered {missing_before - missing_after} night-time rows.\")\n",
        "\n",

        "write_module(\"src/models/lstm_component.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import torch\n",

        "\n",
        "# Residual Correction LSTM\n",
        "class ResidualLSTM(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers):\n",
        "        super(ResidualLSTM, self).__init__()\n",
        "        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(input_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, batch_first=True)\n",
        "        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_dim, 2) # Outputs: [Correction, Uncertainty]\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        out, _ = self.lstm(x)\n",
        "        out = out[:, -1, :]\n",
        "        return self.fc(out)\n",
        "\n",
        "class HeteroscedasticLoss(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def forward(self, pred, target):\n",
        "        delta = pred[:, 0]\n",
        "        log_var = pred[:, 1]\n",
        "        residual = target.squeeze()\n",
        "        precision = torch.exp(-log_var)\n",
        "        loss = 0.5 * precision * (residual - delta)**2 + 0.5 * log_var\n",
        "        return loss.mean()\n",
        "\"\"\")\n",

        "import numpy as np\n",

        "            hidden_dim=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['hidden_dim'],\n",
        "            num_layers=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['num_layers']\n",
        "        )\n",

        "\n",

        "\n",
        "        # 2. Residual Correction (Simplified for demo)\n",

        "        dummy_tensor = torch.FloatTensor(dummy_resid).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.eval()\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            preds = self.lstm_model(dummy_tensor).cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        delta = preds[:, 0] * self.scaler_lstm.scale_[0] # Scale back\n",
        "        sigma = np.sqrt(np.exp(preds[:, 1]))\n",
        "\n",
        "        return y_xgb + delta, sigma\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _create_sequences(self, data, seq_len):\n",
        "        xs, ys = [], []\n",
        "        for i in range(len(data) - seq_len):\n",

        "            y = data[i + seq_len]\n",
        "            xs.append(x)\n",

        "        return torch.FloatTensor(np.array(xs)).to(self.device), torch.FloatTensor(np.array(ys)).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _train_lstm(self, X, y):\n",
        "        optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(self.lstm_model.parameters(), lr=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['learning_rate'])\n",

        "import os\n",
        "\n",
        "PROJECT_ROOT = \"/content/solar_forecast_project\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Helper to overwrite the file\n",
        "def write_module(path, content):\n",
        "    full_path = f\"{PROJECT_ROOT}/{path}\"\n",
        "    with open(full_path, \"w\") as f:\n",
        "        f.write(content)\n",
        "    print(f\"Fixed and Updated: {path}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# FIXED MODULE: src/models/hybrid_system.py\n",
        "# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
        "write_module(\"src/models/hybrid_system.py\", \"\"\"\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader, TensorDataset\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from .xgb_component import XGBModel\n",
        "from .lstm_component import ResidualLSTM, HeteroscedasticLoss\n",
        "from ..config.settings import Config\n",
        "from ..utils.logger import setup_logger\n",
        "\n",
        "logger = setup_logger(\"HybridSystem\")\n",
        "\n",
        "class HybridForecaster:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, input_dim_lstm):\n",
        "        self.xgb_model = XGBModel()\n",
        "        self.lstm_model = ResidualLSTM(\n",
        "            input_dim=input_dim_lstm,\n",
        "            hidden_dim=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['hidden_dim'],\n",
        "            num_layers=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['num_layers']\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm = StandardScaler()\n",
        "        self.device = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def fit(self, X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val):\n",
        "        # Phase 1: XGBoost\n",
        "        logger.info(\"Training XGBoost Base Model...\")\n",
        "        self.xgb_model.fit(X_train, y_train, X_val, y_val)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Phase 2: Residuals\n",
        "        # Returns a Pandas Series\n",
        "        r_train = self.xgb_model.get_residuals(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # FIX: Convert Pandas Series to NumPy array before reshaping\n",
        "        r_train = r_train.values.reshape(-1, 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Prepare LSTM Data\n",
        "        self.scaler_lstm.fit(r_train)\n",
        "        r_train_scaled = self.scaler_lstm.transform(r_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Convert to Tensor sequences\n",
        "        X_lstm, y_lstm = self._create_sequences(r_train_scaled, Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'])\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Phase 3: Train LSTM\n",
        "        logger.info(f\"Training LSTM Residual Corrector on {self.device}...\")\n",
        "        self._train_lstm(X_lstm, y_lstm)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def predict(self, X_df):\n",
        "        # 1. Base Prediction\n",
        "        y_xgb = self.xgb_model.predict(X_df)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 2. Residual Correction\n",
        "        # Creating a dummy tensor for batch prediction speed (Simplified for this demo)\n",
        "        # In a real production system, you would feed the *actual* past residuals here.\n",
        "        dummy_resid = np.zeros((len(X_df), Config.LSTM_PARAMS['lookback_window'], 1))\n",
        "        dummy_tensor = torch.FloatTensor(dummy_resid).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "        self.lstm_model.eval()\n",
        "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "            preds = self.lstm_model(dummy_tensor).cpu().numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "        # 3. Scale back and Combine\n",
        "        delta = preds[:, 0] * self.scaler_lstm.scale_[0]\n",
        "        # Calculate uncertainty (sigma)\n",
        "        sigma = np.sqrt(np.exp(preds[:, 1]))\n",
        "\n",
        "        return y_xgb + delta, sigma\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _create_sequences(self, data, seq_len):\n",
        "        xs, ys = [], []\n",
        "        for i in range(len(data) - seq_len):\n",
        "            x = data[i:(i + seq_len)]\n",
        "            y = data[i + seq_len]\n",
        "            xs.append(x)\n",
        "            ys.append(y)\n",
        "        # Convert to PyTorch Tensors\n",
        "        return torch.FloatTensor(np.array(xs)).to(self.device), torch.FloatTensor(np.array(ys)).to(self.device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _train_lstm(self, X, y):\n",
        "        optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(self.lstm_model.parameters(), lr=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['learning_rate'])\n",
        "        criterion = HeteroscedasticLoss()\n",
        "\n",
        "        dataset = TensorDataset(X, y)\n",
        "        loader = DataLoader(dataset, batch_size=Config.LSTM_PARAMS['batch_size'], shuffle=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "        for epoch in range(Config.LSTM_PARAMS['epochs']):\n",
        "            self.lstm_model.train()\n",
        "            total_loss = 0\n",
        "            for batch_X, batch_y in loader:\n",
        "                optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
        "                preds = self.lstm_model(batch_X)\n",
        "                loss = criterion(preds, batch_y)\n",
        "                loss.backward()\n",
        "                optimizer.step()\n",
        "                total_loss += loss.item()\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Log every 5 epochs\n",
        "            if (epoch + 1) % 5 == 0:\n",
        "                avg_loss = total_loss / len(loader)\n",
        "                logger.info(f\"LSTM Epoch {epoch+1}/{Config.LSTM_PARAMS['epochs']} - Loss: {avg_loss:.4f}\")\n",
        "\"\"\")"
